title: Washington AG sues Facebook for violating state political ad law
text: Washington Attorney General Bob Ferguson filed a new lawsuit against Facebook claiming the social network continues to violate state laws governing political ad disclosures.

title: Even Google and Facebook May be Facing an Ad Slump
text: Though ad sales at the two companies are expected to be down, they are likely to fare better than smaller peers and publishers.

title: Facebook launches an experimental app for messaging close friends over Apple Watch
text: Facebook’s internal R&D group has today launched a new app that lets you keep up with your close friends via your Apple Watch. The app is called Kit, or Keep in Touch, and works using a combination of QR codes and Facebook’s existing Messenger service.

title: Facebook Stock Is a Scorching-Hot Buy Now
text: With businesses moving their ad dollars from traditional to digital media, Facebook is on the winning side of a long-term trend. That means you should buy FB stock now, before shares bounce back to prior highs.

title: Instagram's Revenue Could Overtake the Rest of Facebook's by 2022
text: Instagram is set to grab tons of new digital ad spending.

title: 10 Brand-New Stocks I Bought During the Stock Market Crash
text: Bear markets have always represented an excellent time for investors to go shopping.
